ted to the withdrawal of the political left from traditional working-class communities, and the left’s refusal to advance the economic interests of those who have suffered most from neoliberal economic restructuring. Incisive, contentious and boundary-breaking, it uses the voices of men and women who now support far-right political groups to address the total failure of mainstream parliamentary politics and the rising tide of frustration, resentment and anger.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aRight and left (Political science)xHistoryy20th centuryzGreat Britain. 0aRight and left (Political science)xHistoryy21st centuryzGreat Britain. 0aRight and left (Political science)zGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aRight and left (Political science)zGreat BritainxHistoryy21st century. 0aWorking classxAttitudesxHistoryy20th centuryzGreat Britain. 0aWorking classxAttitudesxHistoryy21st centuryzGreat Britain. 0aWorking classzGreat BritainxAttitudesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorking classzGreat BritainxAttitudesxHistoryy21st century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Political Parties.2bisacsh1 aHall, Steve, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTreadwell, James, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z9783111196435oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144732848340uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447328506?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447328506423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447328506/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPb2016